\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. A. atrata} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 899 (1753). Plant odourless. Stems up to 30 cm, simple, erect, at least the upper part densely brown pubescent. Leaves 1-4 cm, usually 2-pinnatifid; primary segments with not more than 3 lanceolate, acute, distant lobes, subglabrous, not punctate. Corymbs with 2-10 capitula; peduncles 3-15 mm, usually brown-pubescent. Involucre 8-12 mm in diameter; bracts c. 5 mm, lanceolate, with a wide, darkish brown margin. Ligules c. 6 mm, obovate, white. 2n = 18.{\i  Rock-crevices, screes and stony pastures; usually calcicole. • Alps.} Au Ga Ge He It Ju.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   Hybrids with {\b 3}({\b a}) are frequent.
\par

