\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. A. abrotanoides} (Vis.) Vis., {\i Fl. Dalm.}{\b  2}: 81 (1847). Stems up to 40 cm, simple or branched above, erect or ascending, glabrescent. Leaves 1-3 cm, 1(-2)-pinnatifid, mostly cauline, appressed-pubescent; lobes linear to lanceolate, acute, entire. Corymbs with 12-30 capitula; peduncles 6-10 mm. Involucre 5-7 mm in diameter; bracts c. 3 mm, ovate, obtuse, with a narrow, pale brown margin. Ligules c. 4 mm, obovate, white. 2n = 18.{\i  Mountain rocks and screes. W. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Gr Ju.
